A professional membership got me the room for $76/night which, for right-in-the-middle-of-everything-Chicago isn't bad at all.	We've been to Chicago numerous times, but these accomodations were, by far, the best yet.	In terms of location, this place could not be beat in my opinion.	The hotel restaurant is surprisingly good, and makes the famous Chicago deep dish pizza.	I took my 6 year old daughter to Chicago for an end of summer vacation.	My room was super quiet-I never heard another guest during my 48 hour stay.